value.value: A rhodopsin-like G-protein coupled receptor that is a translation product of the human OXGR1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is 2-oxoglutarate (alpha-ketoglutarate).

A 5-hydroxytryptamine receptor that is a translation product of the human HTR1A, HTR1B, HTR1D, HTR1E or HTR1F genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is 5-hydroxytryptamine (serotonin).

A 5-hydroxytryptamine receptor that is a translation product of the human HTR2A, HTR2B, or HTR2C genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is 5-hydroxytryptamine (serotonin).
A 5-hydroxytryptamine receptor that is a translation product of the human HTR4 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is 5-hydroxytryptamine (serotonin).

A 5-hydroxytryptamine receptor that is a translation product of the human HTR5A or HTR5B genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is 5-hydroxytryptamine (serotonin).
A 5-hydroxytryptamine receptor that is a translation product of the human HTR6 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is 5-hydroxytryptamine (serotonin).
A 5-hydroxytryptamine receptor that is a translation product of the human HTR7 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is 5-hydroxytryptamine (serotonin).
A complement peptide receptor that is a translation product of the human C3AR1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is C3a anaphylatoxin.
A complement peptide receptor whose active form binds C5a anaphylatoxin.
A VVC2C2C2 Ig-like domain arrangement-containing protein that is a translation product of the human ALCAM gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A dopamine receptor that is a product of the DRD1 or DRD5 gene. The active form binds dopamine and its activity is mediated by G proteins that cause activation of adenylate cyclase.
A dopamine receptor that is a product of the DRD2, DRD3, or DRD4 gene. The active form binds dopamine and its activity is mediated by G proteins that cause inhibition of adenylate cyclase.
A rhodopsin-like G-protein coupled receptor that is a translation product of the human GPR183 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A G-protein coupled bile acid receptor that is a translation product of the human GPBAR1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligands are bile acids.
A G-protein coupled estrogen receptor that is a translation product of the human GPER1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is estrogen.

A rhodopsin-like G-protein coupled receptor that is a translation product of the human GPR37L1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. Although about 50% identical to prosaposin receptor GPR37 over a carboxyl-terminal span of about 360 residues, the amino-terminal region of about 120 residues is dissimilar and about 120 residues shorter.
An interleukin-17 that is a translation product of the human IL25 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A CD2 molecule that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P06729-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
An adrenoceptor protein whose active form binds adrenaline and related compounds and whose activity is mediated by G proteins that activate a phosphatidylinositol-calcium second messenger system.
An adrenoceptor protein whose active form binds adrenaline and related compounds and whose activity is mediated by G proteins that cause inhibition of adenylate cyclase.

An alpha-latrotoxin that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P23631-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A rhodopsin-like G-protein coupled receptor that is a translation product of the human AGTR1 or AGTR2 genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof. The active form binds angiotensin II.

definition.value: Category=family. Note: Angiotensin II is derived from its precursor, angiotensin I, which is biologically inactive. For this reason the receptor is often referred to as simply angiotensin receptor.

value.value: A rhodopsin-like G-protein coupled receptor that is a translation product of the human OPN1LW, OPN1MW, OPN1SW, RHO, OPN3, OPN4, or OPN5 genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof in Metazoa. The active form binds a vitamin A-based retinaldehyde chromophore through a Schiff base linkage to a Lys residue in the seventh transmembrane alpha helix.
A rhodopsin-like G-protein coupled receptor that is a translation product of the human APLNR gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is apelin.
An adrenoceptor protein whose active form binds adrenaline and related compounds and whose activity is mediated by G proteins that cause activation of adenylate cyclase.

A rhodopsin-like G-protein coupled receptor that is a translation product of the human NMBR, GRPR, or BRS3 genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof. The active form binds bombesin (a 14 amino acid peptide originally isolated from the skin of a frog) or its homologs. Mammalian homologs of bombesin include gastrin-releasing peptide and neuromedin-B.
A rhodopsin-like G-protein coupled receptor that is a translation product of the human BDKRB1 or BDKRB2 genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof. The active form binds bradykinin.
An adhesion G-protein coupled receptor whose active form binds alpha-latrotoxin, an excitatory neurotoxin present in black widow spider venom.

A cannabinoid receptor that is a translation product of the human CNR1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. Preferred ligands are cannabinoids--molecules related to tetrahydrocannabinol (THC), the psychoactive ingredient of cannabis. Endogenous cannabinoids serve as neurotransmitters. This receptor is expressed primarily in the brain.

A cannabinoid receptor that is a translation product of the human CNR2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. Preferred ligands are cannabinoids--molecules related to tetrahydrocannabinol (THC), the psychoactive ingredient of cannabis. This receptor is expressed primarily in the immune system.
A VVC2C2C2 Ig-like domain arrangement-containing protein that is a translation product of the human MCAM gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A rhodopsin-like G-protein coupled receptor that in active form binds to one or more chemokines.

definition.value: Category=family. Note: Only those that have been unequivocally shown to activate a G-protein coupled signaling pathway appear on the official IUPHAR list.

value.value: A chemerin receptor that is a translation product of the human CMKLR1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A rhodopsin-like G-protein coupled receptor that is a translation product of the human CCKAR or CCKBR genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof. The active form binds cholecystokinin (CCK).
A leukotriene receptor that in active form binds cysteinyl leukotriene.
A chemokine receptor that is a translation product of the human ACKR1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. This is a non-specific, non-signaling chemokine receptor.
A rhodopsin-like G-protein coupled receptor that is a translation product of the human EDNRA or EDNRB genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or pro-orthologs thereof. The active form binds endothelins.

definition.value: Category=family. Pro-orthology refers to, in this case, after-speciation gene duplication in the non-human species (aka 1:many orthology).

value.value: A rhodopsin-like G-protein coupled receptor whose active form binds either growth hormone secretagogues (principally ghrelin) or motilin. The motilin and ghrelin receptors are about 45% identical in amino acid sequence.
An interleukin-1 that is a translation product of the human IL1A gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. Critical mediator of the immune and inflammatory responses.
An interleukin-1 that is a translation product of the human IL1B gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A protein that is a translation product of the human IL1RN gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

definition.value: Category=gene. Note: The active form inhibits the activity of IL-1 by binding to its receptor.

value.value: An interleukin-17 that is a translation product of the human IL17A gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The active product is a proinflammatory cytokine produced by activated T cells. This cytokine regulates the activities of NF-kappaB and mitogen-activated protein kinases.
An interleukin-17 that is a translation product of the human IL17B gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
An interleukin-17 that is a translation product of the human IL17C gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
An interleukin-17 that is a translation product of the human IL17D gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
An interleukin-17 that is a translation product of the human IL17F gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A VVC2C2C2 Ig-like domain arrangement-containing protein that is a translation product of the human BCAM gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A melanin-concentrating hormone receptor that is a translation product of the human MCHR1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is melanin-concentrating hormone. This receptor is expressed in all mammals.

A melanin-concentrating hormone receptor that is a translation product of the human MCHR2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is melanin-concentrating hormone. This receptor is expressed in humans and in some primates and carnivores.

A rhodopsin-like G-protein coupled receptor that is a translation product of the human MC1R to MC5R genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof. The active form binds one or more melanocortins, the pituitary peptides ACTH and alpha-, beta-, and gamma-melanocyte-stimulating hormone.
